Quarterfinals (1934\u20131938, 1954\u20131970, and 1986\u2013present: knockout round of 8)\n*R2 &mdash; Round 2 (1974&ndash;1978, second group stage, top 8; 1982: second group stage, top 12; 1986\u2013present: knockout round of 16)\n*R1 &mdash; Round 1\n{{col-2}}\n*Q &mdash; Qualified for upcoming tournament\n*{{border|width=1px|color=gray|&nbsp;\u2022\u2022&nbsp;}} &mdash; Qualified but withdrew\n*{{border|width=1px|color=gray|&nbsp;\u2022&nbsp;}} &mdash; Did not qualify\n*{{border|width=1px|color=gray|&nbsp;\u00d7&nbsp;}} &mdash; Did not enter / Withdrew / Banned\n*{{border|width=3px|color=red|&nbsp;&nbsp;}} &mdash; Hosts\n*{{border|width=1px|color=gray|&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;}} &mdash; Not affiliated in FIFA\n{{col-end}}\n\nThe team ranking in each tournament is according to FIFA.<ref>{{cite web\n| last = \n| first = \n| authorlink = \n| vauthors = \n| date = \n| year = \n| month = \n| url = https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/fifafacts/mcwc/ip-301%5f01a%5ffwc-stats%5fnew%5f8865.pdf\n| title = FIFA World Cup Statistical Overview (page 4)\n| format = PDF\n| work = \n| pages = \n| publisher = \n| language = \n| accessdate = May 17, 2006\n}}</ref> The rankings, apart from the top four positions (top two in 1930), are not a result of direct competition between the teams; instead, teams eliminated in the same round are ranked by their full results in the tournament. In recent tournaments, FIFA has used the rankings for seedings for the final tournament draw.<ref>[https://www.fifa.com/mm/document/tournament/finaldraw/02/23/84/73/131203_finaldrawprocedures_neutral.pdf.pdf Seeding of national teams (PDF)]. Accessed 12 September 2016.</ref>\n\nFor each tournament, the number of teams in each finals tournament (in brackets) are shown.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; font-size:90%\"\n|-\n! Team\n![[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]]<br>{{Flagicon|Uruguay}}<br>(13)\n![[1934 FIFA World Cup|1934]]<br>{{Flagicon|Italy|1861}}<br>(16)\n![[1938 FIFA World Cup|1938]]<br>{{Flagicon|France|1794}}<br>(15)\n![[1950 FIFA World Cup|1950]]<br>{{Flagicon|Brazil|1889}}<br>(13)\n![[1954 FIFA World Cup|1954]]<br>{{Flagicon|Switzerland}}<br>(16)\n![[1958 FIFA World Cup|1958]]<br>{{Flagicon|Sweden}}<br>(16)\n![[1962 FIFA World Cup|1962]]<br>{{Flagicon|Chile}}<br>(16)\n![[1966 FIFA World Cup|1966]]<br>{{Flagicon|England}}<br>(16)\n![[1970 FIFA World Cup|1970]]<br>{{Flagicon|Mexico}}<br>(16)\n![[1974 FIFA World Cup|1974]]<br>{{Flagicon|West Germany}}<br>(16)\n![[1978 FIFA World Cup|1978]]<br>{{Flagicon|Argentina}}<br>(16)\n![[1982 FIFA World Cup|1982]]<br>{{Flagicon|Spain}}<br>(24)\n![[1986 FIFA World Cup|1986]]<br>{{Flagicon|Mexico}}<br>(24)\n![[1990 FIFA World Cup|1990]]<br>{{Flagicon|Italy}}<br>(24)\n![[1994 FIFA World Cup|1994]]<br>{{Flagicon|USA}}<br>(24)\n![[1998 FIFA World Cup|1998]]<br>{{Flagicon|France}}<br>(32)\n![[2002 FIFA World Cup|2002]]<br>{{Flagicon|South Korea|1997}}<br>{{Flagicon|Japan}}<br>(32)\n![[2006 FIFA World Cup|2006]]<br>{{Flagicon|Germany}}<br>(32)\n![[2010 FIFA World Cup|2010]]<br>{{Flagicon|South Africa}}<br>(32)\n![[2014 FIFA World Cup|2014]]<br>{{Flagicon|Brazil}}<br>(32)\n![[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]]<br>{{Flagicon|Russia}}<br>(32)\n![[2022 FIFA World Cup|2022]]<br>{{Flagicon|Qatar}}<br>(32)\n!Total\n!Qual.<br>Comp.\n|-\n| id=\"ALG\" style=\"text-align:left;\"| {{fb|ALG}}\n|colspan=7| ''Former colony of France''<ref>''[[Algeria]]'' gained independence in 1962, but they joined with other African nations to boycott the [[1966 FIFA World Cup]]. Thus the [[1970 FIFA World Cup qualification]] was their first participation.</ref> ||\u00d7||\u2022||\u2022||\u2022|| R1<br>{{small|13th}} || R1<br>{{small|22nd}} ||\u2022||\u2022||\u2022||\u2022||\u2022|| R1<br>{{small|28th}} || R2<br>{{small|14th}} ||\u2022|| || '''4''' || 13\n|-\n| id=\"ANG\" style=\"text-align:left;\"| {{fb|ANG}}\n|colspan=11| ''Former colony of Portugal'' ||\u00d7||\u2022||\u2022||\u2022||\u2022||\u2022|| R1<br>{{small|23rd}} ||\u2022||\u2022||\u2022|| || '''1'