\u00d7||\u2022||\u2022||\u2022||\u2022\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: left;\" | {{fb|CTA}} || '''3''' || || || || || || || ||\u00d7||\u00d7||\u00d7||\u00d7||\u00d7||\u00d7||\u00d7||\u00d7||\u00d7||\u00d7||\u00d7||\u00d7||\u2022||\u2022||\n|-\n| style=\"text-align: left;\" | {{fb|SSD}} || '''2''' || colspan=19| ''part of Sudan'' ||\u00d7||\u2022||\u2022\n|-\n|}\n\n==Summary of performance==\n\nThis table shows for each world cup the number of countries at the World Cup, the number of entries (#E) from around the world (including any rejections and withdrawals), the number of African entries (#A), how many of those African entries withdrew (#A-) before/during qualification or were rejected by [[FIFA]], the African representatives at the World Cup finals, the number of World Cup Qualifiers each African representative had to play to get to the World Cup (#WCQ), the furthest stage they reached, their results, and their coaches.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"1\" cellpadding=\"2\"\n|-\n! Year !! Host !! Size !! #E !! #A !! ''#A-'' || African<br>finalists !! #WCQ !! Stage !! Results !! Coach\n|-\n|[[1930 FIFA World Cup|1930]] ||Uruguay||13||13||0||''0''|| - || || || ||\n|-\n|[[1934 FIFA World Cup|1934]] ||Italy||16|| [[1934 FIFA World Cup qualification|32]] || 1 ||''0''|| {{fb|EGY|1922}} || 2 || R1 || lost 2\u20134 {{fb|HUN|1920}} || {{flagicon|SCO}} [[James McRea]]\n|-\n|[[1938 FIFA World Cup|1938]] ||France||15|| [[1938 FIFA World Cup qualification|37]] || 1 || ''1''<ref>During qualification for the [[1938 FIFA World Cup]], [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]] withdrew before playing any matches.</ref> || - || || || ||\n|-\n|[[1950 FIFA World Cup|1950]] ||Brazil||13|| [[1950 FIFA World Cup qualification|34]] || 0 || ''0''|| - || || || ||\n|-\n|[[1954 FIFA World Cup|1954]] ||Switzerland||16|| [[1954 FIFA World Cup qualification|45]] || [[1954 FIFA World Cup qualification#Group 9|1]] ||''0''||- || || || ||\n|-\n|[[1958 FIFA World Cup|1958]] ||Sweden||16|| [[1958 FIFA World Cup qualification|56]] || [[1958 FIFA World Cup qualification#Africa and Asia|3]] ||''3''<ref>During qualification for the [[1958 FIFA World Cup]], [[Ethiopia national football team|Ethiopia]]'s application was rejected by FIFA, while [[Egypt national football team|Egypt]] and [[Sudan national football team|Sudan]] withdrew after early wins, the latter in protest at having to play [[Israel national football team|Israel]].</ref>||- || || || ||\n|-\n|[[1962 FIFA World Cup|1962]] ||Chile||16||[[1962 FIFA World Cup qualification|56]] || [[1962 FIFA World Cup qualification#Africa|7]] ||''2''<ref>During qualification for the [[1962 FIFA World Cup]], [[Sudan national football team|Sudan]] and the [[Egypt national football team|United Arab Republic]] (Egypt) tried to rearrange matches to avoid the monsoon season; FIFA refused to approve this, and they withdrew in protest without playing any matches.</ref> || - || || || ||\n|-\n|[[1966 FIFA World Cup|1966]] ||England||16||[[1966 FIFA World Cup qualification|74]] || [[1966 FIFA World Cup qualification (Africa, Asia and Oceania)|17]] ||''17''<ref>During qualification for [[1966 FIFA World Cup]], [[Congo national football team|French Congo]]'s entry was rejected, and [[South Africa national football team|South Africa]] were subsequently disqualified after being suspended due to apartheid. The remaining 15  African countries in the competition later withdrew without playing any matches to protest FIFA's failure to allocate a World Cup spot to an African team.</ref> ||colspan=5 align=center| ''Boycott''\n|-\n|colspan=11|\n|-\n|[[1970 FIFA World Cup|1970]] ||Mexico||16|| [[1970 FIFA World Cup qualification|75]] || [[1970 FIFA World Cup qualification#Africa .28CAF.29|14]] || ''2''<ref>[[FIFA]] rejected the applications of [[Guinea national football team|Guinea]] and [[DR Congo national football team|Zaire]] for the [[1970 FIFA World Cup]].</ref> ||{{fb|MAR}} || 10 || R1 || lost 1\u20132 {{fb|FRG}}, lost 0\u20133 {{fb|PE