||rowspan=5| [[1998 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|38]] ||rowspan=5|''3''<ref>During qualification for the [[1998 FIFA World Cup]], [[Mali national football team|Mali]] and [[Niger national football team|Niger]] withdrew without playing a match. War-torn [[Burundi national football team|Burundi]] withdrew after having won two matches and having qualified for the second round.</ref> || {{fb|CMR}} || 6 ||R1||''drew 1\u20131'' {{fb|AUT}}, lost 0\u20133 {{fb|ITA}}, ''drew 1\u20131'' {{fb|CHI}} || {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Claude Le Roy]]\n|-\n| {{fb|MAR}} ||6 ||R1|| ''drew 2\u20132'' {{fb|NOR}}, lost 0\u20133 {{fb|BRA}}, '''won 3\u20130''' {{fb|SCO}} ||{{flagicon|FRA}} [[Henri Michel]]\n|-\n| {{fb|NGA}} || 6 ||R2||'''won 3\u20132''' {{fb|ESP}}, '''won 1\u20130''' {{fb|BUL}}, lost 1\u20133 {{fb|PAR|1990}} <br> R2: lost 1\u20134 {{fb|DEN}} ||  {{flagicon|FR Yugoslavia}} [[Bora Milutinovic]]\n|-\n| {{fb|RSA}} || 8 ||R1||lost 0\u20133 {{fb|FRA}}, ''drew 1\u20131'' {{fb|DEN}}, ''drew 2\u20132'' {{fb|KSA}} || {{flagicon|FRA}} [[Philippe Troussier]]\n|-\n| {{fb|TUN|1959}} || 8 ||R1||lost 0\u20132 {{fb|ENG}}, lost 0\u20131 {{fb|COL}}, ''drew 1\u20131'' {{fb|ROM}} || {{flagicon|POL}} [[Henryk Kasperczak]]\n|-\n|colspan=11|\n|-\n|rowspan=5|[[2002 FIFA World Cup|2002]]||rowspan=5|South Korea<br>and Japan||rowspan=5|32|| rowspan=5|[[2002 FIFA World Cup qualification|199]] ||rowspan=5| [[2002 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|51]] ||rowspan=5|''2''<ref>During qualification for the [[2002 FIFA World Cup]], [[Burundi national football team|Burundi]] withdrew before the draw was made and thus played no matches. [[Guinea national football team|Guinea]] was disqualified by [[FIFA]] after they had played five matches because the Guinea Football Association was suspended due to political interference.</ref> || {{fb|CMR}} || 10 ||R1||''drew 1\u20131'' {{fb|IRL}}, '''won 1\u20130''' {{fb|KSA}}, lost 0\u20132 {{fb|GER}} || {{flagicon|GER}} [[Winfried Sch\u00e4fer]]\n|-\n| {{fb|NGA}} || 10 ||R1|