t playing any matches.</ref> || {{fb|ALG}} || 6 ||R1||''drew 1\u20131'' {{fb|NIR}}, lost 0\u20131 {{fb|BRA|1968}}, lost 0\u20133 {{fb|ESP}} || {{flagicon|ALG}} [[Rabah Sa\u00e2dane]]\n|-\n| {{fb|MAR}} || 8 ||R2||''drew 0\u20130'' {{fb|POL|1980}}, ''drew 0\u20130'' {{fb|ENG}}, '''win 3\u20131''' {{fb|POR}}<br> R2: lost 0\u20131 {{fb|FRG}} ||{{flagicon|BRA|1968}}[[Jos\u00e9 Faria]]\n|-\n|colspan=11|\n|-\n|rowspan=2|[[1990 FIFA World Cup|1990]]||rowspan=2|Italy||rowspan=2|24|| rowspan=2|[[1990 FIFA World Cup qualification|116]] ||rowspan=2| [[1990 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|26]] || rowspan=2|''5''<ref>During qualification for the [[1990 FIFA World Cup]], [[FIFA]] rejected the applications of [[Mauritius national football team|Mauritius]] and [[Mozambique national football team|Mozambique]] due to outstanding financial debts. [[Lesotho national football team|Lesotho]], [[Rwanda national football team|Rwanda]], and [[Togo national football team|Togo]] withdrew without playing, while [[Libya national football team|Libya]] withdrew during the second round after playing three matches.</ref> ||{{fb|CMR}} || 8 ||QF||'''won 1\u20130''' {{fb|ARG}}, '''won 2\u20131''' {{fb|ROM}}, lost 0\u20134 {{fb|URS}}<br> R2: '''won 2\u20131''' {{fb|COL}}, QF: lost 2\u20133 (a.e.t.) {{fb|ENG}} ||{{flagicon|URS}} [[Valeri Nepomniachi]]\n|-\n| {{fb|EGY}} || 8 ||R1||''drew 1\u20131'' {{fb|NED}}, ''drew 0\u20130'' {{fb|IRL}}, lost 0\u20131 {{fb|ENG}} || {{flagicon|EGY}} [[Mahmoud El-Gohary]]\n|-\n|colspan=11|\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[1994 FIFA World Cup|1994]]||rowspan=3|U.S.||rowspan=3|24|| rowspan=3|[[1994 FIFA World Cup qualification|147]] ||rowspan=3| [[1994 FIFA World Cup qualification (CAF)|40]] ||rowspan=3|''12''<ref>During qualification for the [[1994 FIFA World Cup]], [[Libya national football team|Libya]] was disqualified owing to [[United Nations|UN]] sanctions. [[Burkina Faso national football team|Burkina Faso]], [[Malawi national football team|Malawi]], [[S\u00e3o Tom\u00e9 and Pr\